## Python (Layer 3 — environment)

- **Always use a virtual environment** (`python -m venv .venv`, or uv/poetry). Never install into system Python.
- Activate it before working; keep `.venv/` git-ignored. Pin deps in a lockfile.
- Why: isolates project deps, avoids version clashes across projects, and makes installs reproducible.
- Manage interpreter versions with **pyenv** when you need multiple Python versions.

> For exact commands on your OS, query **context7** (or the venv/uv/poetry docs).
